A  quinocycline  antibiotic,  kosinostatin,  was  isolated  from  the  culture  broth  of Micromonospora  sp.  TP-A0468  along  with  isoquinocycline  B.  Structure  of  kosinostatin  was determined to be  the stereoisomer  of isoquinocycline  B regarding to the  stereochemistry at  the C-2'  spiro carbon by NMR  analysis. Kosinostatin isomerizes to isoquinocycline  B through  the inversion of the  stereocenter at C-2'.  Comparison of physico-chemical properties indicated that kosinostatin  is  presumably  identical  with  quinocycline  B  isolated  by  CELMER et  al.  from Streptomyces aureofaciens.
